The paper proposes a novel approach for multi-task clustering using machine learning techniques. The paper discusses the use of self-paced learning and soft clustering to improve the clustering performance. This work is related to several sub-categories of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), natural language processing (cs.CL), computer vision (cs.CV), and social and information networks (cs.SI). However, given the focus on machine learning and clustering, cs.LG is the most likely sub-category, followed by cs.AI and cs.CL.
